      • changeScene

        public static javafx.fxml.FXMLLoader changeScene​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event,
                                                 java.lang.String fxmlFileName,
                                                 java.lang.String windowTitle)
                                          throws java.io.IOException
        Switches scene to Create New Part or Product form.
        Parameters:
        event - the user generated event (a button being clicked) that caused this to execute
        fxmlFileName - the .fxml file holding the next scene
        windowTitle - the new window title to set
        Returns:
        FXML Loader for use when getting the controller
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if .fxml filename cannot be found

      • changeScenePassPart

        public static void changeScenePassPart​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event,
                                       Part passedPart,
                                       java.lang.String fxmlFileName,
                                       java.lang.String windowTitle)
                                throws java.io.IOException
        Switches scene to Modify Part form.

        The fields are populated with data from the existing part that is to be edited.

        Parameters:
        event - the user generated event (a button being clicked) that caused this to execute
        passedPart - the part to modify
        fxmlFileName - the .fxml file holding the next scene
        windowTitle - the new window title to set
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if .fxml filename cannot be found
        See Also:
        PartController.setExistingPart(Part)

      • confirmDeletion

        public static void confirmDeletion​(java.lang.String title,
                                   java.lang.String header,
                                   java.lang.String content,
                                   java.util.function.BooleanSupplier lambda)
        Displays a confirmation dialog for removing or deleting parts or products.

        When the user confirms by clicking "OK", the lambda function will execute. If the lambda returns false, this indicates the delete operation was not successful. In this case an error dialog is shown.

        Parameters:
        title - Dialog box window title
        header - Dialog box header text
        content - details within confirmation dialog box
        lambda - the operation to execute when the user clicks "OK"
